metadata.name: gm
metadata.description: To sign "GM" in ASL, you can first sign the letter G by making a fist with your dominant hand and extending your pinky and thumb fingers out straight, then bringing them together to touch, as if you were forming a hook. Then, without putting your hand down, transition into the sign for the letter M by extending your pointer and middle fingers out straight and bringing them together to touch at the tips, forming two peaks.
